  "datePublished": "2026-03-04",
  "description": "Repeatability improves the interpretability of presence-only data. Consistent effort over time and space reduces bias and supports stronger inferences.\n¶Practice guidance Revisit the same sites across seasons to capture phenology. Document effort (time spent, route, conditions) in observation notes. Avoid “drive-by” records when a focused survey is feasible. ¶Effort metadata that increases scientific value Time spent observing and approximate area covered. Weather or light conditions that affect detectability. Search method (transect, opportunistic, stationary). ¶Cadence guidance: daily to annual practice Daily\n",
  "name": "Repeatability: temporal and spatial consistency",
